---
import CaseStudyLayout from '../../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro';
---

<CaseStudyLayout org="HBO" role="Lead UX Designer" year="2015–2019">

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Context</span>
    <h2 class="cs-section-title">A premium brand navigating the streaming transition</h2>
    <p>HBO was shifting from a linear cable model to direct-to-consumer streaming with HBO NOW and HBO GO. The product experience hadn't kept pace — rigid information architecture, limited content discovery, and no connected-TV design language. Then AT&T acquired Time Warner, and everything had to be re-evaluated against an eventual HBO Max launch.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">My Scope</span>
    <div class="cs-scope-grid">
      <div class="cs-scope-item">
        <span class="cs-scope-label">Team</span>
        <span class="cs-scope-value">4 UX designers, UX research, photo retouching team, cross-functional partners in Product, Engineering, and Programming</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-scope-item">
        <span class="cs-scope-label">Reporting</span>
        <span class="cs-scope-value">UX Lead reporting to VP of Product</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-scope-item">
        <span class="cs-scope-label">Org Placement</span>
        <span class="cs-scope-value">Central product design within HBO Digital Products</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-scope-item">
        <span class="cs-scope-label">Influence</span>
        <span class="cs-scope-value">Cross-platform — owned experience across desktop, mobile, tablet, and connected TV</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Strategic Challenge</span>
    <h2 class="cs-section-title">A content library users couldn't navigate</h2>
    <p>HBO's content catalog was world-class, but its digital experience made discovery nearly impossible. The information architecture was rigid — content lived in silos that didn't map to how users actually thought about shows, movies, and specials. Programming teams resisted navigation changes that threatened their "top-tier" positioning. Meanwhile, the average streaming user spent 7.4 minutes just trying to find something to watch.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Strategic Moves</span>
    <ul>
      <li>Led a platform-wide information architecture overhaul — introduced card sorting and tree testing to validate a flexible, user-centered navigation model that added 10 new genres and shifted from 1:1 to many-to-many content tagging</li>
      <li>Designed and prototyped a digital channel surfing feature that converted the catalog into surfable channels, reducing decision fatigue — concept received U.S. Patent #11,006,182</li>
      <li>Served as Apple launch partner for tvOS — led dynamic video backgrounds, parallax focus tiles (LCR format), and batch automation tooling for layered key art across the entire HBO catalog</li>
      <li>Shipped an interactive video player for VICE News Tonight, enabling secondary content (video, infographics, documents) alongside primary segments — framework adopted by other HBO programs for 2+ years</li>
      <li>Managed stakeholder alignment across Programming, Marketing, and Technology — navigating organizational resistance through research evidence and incremental pilots</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Impact</span>
    <div class="cs-metrics">
      <div class="cs-metric">
        <span class="cs-metric-value">4x</span>
        <span class="cs-metric-label">Content discoverability increase</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-metric">
        <span class="cs-metric-value">1</span>
        <span class="cs-metric-label">U.S. Patent granted</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-metric">
        <span class="cs-metric-value">4</span>
        <span class="cs-metric-label">Major shipped initiatives</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-metric">
        <span class="cs-metric-value">5</span>
        <span class="cs-metric-label">Platforms redesigned</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>The IA overhaul fundamentally changed how users discovered HBO content — a show like Last Week Tonight became findable in 12 locations vs. 3 previously. The interactive player framework outlived the original VICE partnership, becoming a reusable tool for editorial teams. The tvOS launch established HBO's first native connected-TV design language.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Selected Visual Evidence</span>
    <div class="cs-visuals">
      <div class="cs-visual">
        <img src="/images/projects/hbo-ia-hero.png" alt="HBO NOW — redesigned connected TV top shelf" />
        <span class="cs-visual-caption">Redesigned HBO NOW top shelf on Apple TV after information architecture overhaul</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-visual">
        <img src="/images/projects/hbo-ia-diagram.png" alt="HBO information architecture diagram" />
        <span class="cs-visual-caption">Revised information architecture enabling flexible, multi-path content discovery</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-visual">
        <img src="/images/projects/hbo-surf-wires.jpg" alt="Digital channel surfing wireframes" />
        <span class="cs-visual-caption">Wireframes for the patented digital channel surfing feature on connected TV</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</CaseStudyLayout>
